In [13]:
def all_bert_hidden_states(texts):
    if isinstance(texts,str):
        texts = [texts]
    input_feature = tokenizer(texts,padding='max_length',truncation=True,return_tensors='pt',max_length=30)
    input_feature = {k:v.cuda() for k,v in input_feature.items()}
    with torch.no_grad():
        last_hidden_state,pooler_output,hidden_states = model(**input_feature,output_hidden_states=True)
    return last_hidden_state,pooler_output,hidden_states
In [14]:
layers_emb = {f'layer{i}':[] for i in range(13)}
In [15]:
test_sents = test_df['text'].tolist()
bth_sz = 32
last_hidden_state,pooler_output = [],[]

for idx in range(0,len(test_sents),bth_sz):
    texts = test_sents[idx:idx+bth_sz]
    lhs,po,hs = all_bert_hidden_states(texts)
    last_hidden_state.append(lhs.cpu())
    pooler_output.append(po.cpu())
    for layer in range(13):
        layers_emb[f'layer{layer}'].append(hs[layer].cpu())
In [16]:
from MulticoreTSNE import MulticoreTSNE as TSNE
In [17]:
labels = test_df['cls'].tolist()
In [20]:
hidden_vis_lst = []

for i in range(13):
    print('processing for layer {}'.format(i))
    tsne = TSNE(n_jobs=16)
    hidden_stat = torch.cat(layers_emb[f'layer{i}'],dim=0)
    #Pool strategy: average
    hidden_stat = hidden_stat.mean(dim=1)
    hidden_vis = tsne.fit_transform(hidden_stat)
    hidden_vis_lst.append(hidden_vis)
    plt.scatter(hidden_vis[:,0],hidden_vis[:,1],s=1,c=labels,cmap='jet')
    plt.savefig('layer_{}.png'.format(i))
    plt.show()
